I think people consume too much, and don‚Äôt create enough. This is bad I think.
Like, really rough. But I kept typing; pouring inane, kindergarten-level drivel into my phone.
I know a little bit about the ‚Äúsales funnel.‚Äù‚Ä¶you need 500 cold calls to make three sales. You need to write 500 words to get three good ones. Or 500 sketches, business ideas, or recipes. If you‚Äôre really really good, you can increase your overall conversion rate from 0.6% to 1%‚Äîbut the most reliable way to get better results is to just produce more crap. So I kept at it. week after week. Sometime in the middle of the fourth week I had 3,000 words in my Notes app. That‚Äôs when I started editing. Editing is hard because you realize how bad you are. But editing is easy because we‚Äôre all better at criticizing than we are at creating. The good thing about forcing yourself to produce a bunch of garbage is that you don‚Äôt feel bad deleting it. You‚Äôre not married to any of your work, because you wrote it half-awake on the 1BX while some crazy dude negotiated his fare with the driver. I gleefully deleted hundreds of words, trying not to think about the neanderthal who must‚Äôve written them.</p>
</blockquote>

